---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Curacao Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/curacao/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Aruba for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/aruba' },
  { title: 'Netherlands for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/netherlands' },
  { title: 'Barbados for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/barbados' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'curacaoFit', header: 'Curacao Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'ANG$785-1,120/mo', curacaoFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'ANG$920-1,315/mo', curacaoFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'ANG$705-1,005/mo', curacaoFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'ANG$655-935/mo', curacaoFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'SVB/BZV (Local)', entryAge: 'No limit', renewal: 'Mandatory', monthlyFrom: 'ANG$150-350/mo', curacaoFit: 'For Residents' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'ANG$705-1,120', annual: 'ANG$8,460-13,440' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'ANG$965-1,490', annual: 'ANG$11,580-17,880' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'ANG$1,300-2,005', annual: 'ANG$15,600-24,060' },
  { category: 'BZV Public Insurance', monthly: 'ANG$150-350/mo', annual: 'Income-based' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Stay', monthly: 'ANG$1,200-2,500/day', annual: 'Per incident' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Curacao 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Curacao. Dutch Caribbean, colorful architecture, affordable beaches, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Curacao"
  subheadline="Curacao offers Dutch Caribbean charm, UNESCO World Heritage architecture, beautiful diving, and more affordable living than neighboring islands—a distinctive retirement destination."
  heroImage="/images/countries/curacao-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Curacao</h2>
  <p>
    Curacao offers Dutch-Caribbean culture, colorful Willemstad architecture (UNESCO World Heritage), world-class diving, and more affordable living than Aruba. Outside hurricane belt like its neighbors, Curacao provides Caribbean retirement with European governance.
  </p>

  <p>
    Willemstad is the capital with historic Handelskade waterfront. Banda Abou (west) offers quieter beaches. Jan Thiel has resort community. Pietermaai is trendy urban renewal area. The island is larger than Aruba (171 sq miles) with more variety.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Good for Caribbean; CMC Hospital</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Dutch, Papiamento, English widely spoken</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> ANG$4,000-8,000/month (~$2,200-4,400 USD); moderate</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Tropical desert; sunny; outside hurricane belt</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Multicultural; historic; diving paradise</li>
      <li><strong>Dutch Connection:</strong> Part of Kingdom of Netherlands</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Curacao Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Curacao has good healthcare—Curacao Medical Center (CMC) is the main hospital, newly built with modern equipment. Most routine care handled locally. Complex cases may require Colombia, Miami, or Netherlands. Healthcare quality exceeds most Caribbean islands.
  </p>

  <p>
    BZV is the mandatory basic health insurance for residents. Premiums are income-based. Covers local care; some overseas referrals. Additional international insurance recommended for US/Europe access and complex conditions.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">BZV System</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Curacao has mandatory BZV health insurance for residents—income-based premiums. Covers local care at CMC and some overseas treatment. System is similar to Aruba's AZV. Supplemental international insurance recommended for comprehensive coverage.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Curacao offers residence options:
  </p>

  <h3>Retiree Residence Permit</h3>
  <p>
    For those with guaranteed pension/income. Demonstrate financial independence. Application through immigration.
  </p>

  <h3>Investor/Entrepreneur Permit</h3>
  <p>
    For those investing in Curacao business or property. Various thresholds apply.
  </p>

  <h3>Dutch Citizens</h3>
  <p>
    Kingdom of Netherlands citizenship allows settlement. Registration required.
  </p>

  <h3>Temporary Stay</h3>
  <p>
    Many nationalities receive 30-90 days visa-free. Extensions available.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Curacao:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Residents:</strong> BZV mandatory for all residents</li>
    <li><strong>Permits:</strong> May require private insurance proof</li>
    <li><strong>Supplemental:</strong> Recommended for international access</li>
    <li><strong>Overseas care:</strong> Include US/Netherlands coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Curacao</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      BZV provides local base coverage. International insurance supplements with US/Europe access. CMC handles most conditions; complex cases may need evacuation. Colombia is nearby alternative. Dutch connection provides European options.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Curacao, BZV plus supplemental recommended:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Curacao</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>BZV:</strong> Mandatory local coverage; income-based</li>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Americas + worldwide coverage</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>CMC:</strong> Modern hospital handles most needs locally</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare supplemental coverage for Curacao.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs in Curacao (ANG pegged ~1.79 to USD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>BZV reliance:</strong> Mandatory coverage handles basics</li>
    <li><strong>CMC focus:</strong> Modern hospital for local care</li>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> Reduce supplemental costs</li>
    <li><strong>Colombia option:</strong> Nearby quality alternative</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: Dutch Retiree, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> €2,800/month pension. Dutch citizenship. Willemstad.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BZV mandatory + EHIC for Netherlands visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> BZV ~ANG$250/month. Kingdom connection; affordable Caribbean.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: American Diver, 70</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $3,800/month income. Retiree permit. Jan Thiel area.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BZV + Cigna Global for US coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> BZV + ~ANG$900/month supplement. Diving lifestyle; US backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Venezuelan Professional, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,800/month income. Investor permit. Pietermaai.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BZV + Allianz Care for regional coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> BZV + ~ANG$750/month. Close to Venezuela; Caribbean home.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How does Curacao compare to Aruba?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Similar climate and Dutch connection but different character. Curacao is larger, more affordable, less touristy. Aruba more developed, pricier. Curacao has better diving, more historic architecture. Both outside hurricane belt.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is the new CMC hospital good?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—Curacao Medical Center opened in 2019, replacing old St. Elisabeth Hospital. Modern equipment, Dutch-trained doctors. Handles most conditions locally. Significant improvement over previous facilities.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Curacao safe?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Generally safe—tourist areas and residential neighborhoods are secure. Some crime in specific Willemstad neighborhoods. Exercise normal urban caution. Overall safer than many Caribbean destinations.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What language do I need?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        English widely spoken—sufficient for daily life. Papiamento is local language; Dutch is official. Spanish common due to South American proximity. Most locals speak 4+ languages.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for Curacao coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Curacao authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
